                    "node": {
                        "created_at": "1763971202",
                        "id": "18087831145788407",
                        "text": "Tokyo Food Top 5!\nNumber 5: BAR CENTIFOLIA.\nA refined performance crafted by Japan\u2019s top bartender. A must-visit place at least once in your life.\nNumber 4: Shunya-chan.\nA rare street-style ramen shop in Tokyo! The clear broth is so delicious you can drink it all up!\nNumber 3: Marushichi.\nThe thickest katsudon in Japan! Full of volume, with tender, juicy meat that\u2019s perfect for a hearty meal!\nNumber 2: Benitsuru.\nA long-loved spot for its iconic triple-layered bacon egg pancakes! A must-try, but reservations are essential.\nNumber 1: Ikura.\nEnjoy the live cooking experience of omelette rice on a hot plate! The perfect pairing of omelette and hamburger steak is amazing!\nMake sure to check them out!\n\nspecial thanks\u2192\n@hiropei7\n@nanokawatanabe\n@baebae_gurume\n\n#japantravels #japanfood #visitjapan #japanesefood #asakusa #asakusafood #japaneserestaurant #JapanTravel #traveljapan #tokyocafe #tokyofood"
                    }
                }
            ]
